summary: Warriors oust Rockets for Western Conference finals
title: Warriors oust Rockets for Western Conference finals
body:
Warriors oust Rockets for Western Conference finals

Stephen Curry scored all 33 of his points in the second half as the Golden State Warriors shook off the absence of Kevin Durant to beat the Houston Rockets 118-113 and advance to the Western Conference finals.

The two-time defending champions punched their ticket to the NBA’s final four for the fifth consecutive season and eliminated the Rockets from the postseason for the fourth time in five…
